{"body": [{"indent": 0, "text": ["point"], "type": "title", "level": 0}, {"indent": 0, "type": "summary", "text": ["Returns the value of a point attribute."]}, {"body": [{"body": [{"indent": 4, "type": "para", "text": [{"text": ["surface_node"], "type": "var"}, " is a path to a surface node, for example ", {"text": ["\"/obj/geo1/grid1\""], "type": "code"}, "."]}, {"indent": 4, "type": "para", "text": [{"text": ["point_number"], "type": "var"}, " is the point number to read the attribute from.\n    When instancing, you can use ", {"text": "", "value": "/expressions/instancepoint", "fallback_text": "instancepoint()", "fullpath": "/expressions/instancepoint", "scheme": "Exp", "type": "link"}, " to get the number of the\n    point currently being instanced."]}, {"indent": 4, "type": "para", "text": [{"text": ["attribute"], "type": "var"}, " is the name of the attribute (for example, ", {"text": ["Cd"], "type": "code"}, " for diffuse\n    color). Two special attributes exist: ", {"text": ["P"], "type": "code"}, " and ", {"text": ["Pw"], "type": "code"}, " which represent the\n    position of the point in space (", {"text": ["Pw"], "type": "code"}, " allows you to access the W\n    component of the position)."]}, {"indent": 0, "type": "para", "text": [{"text": ["index"], "type": "var"}, " specifies the component position in multi-component attributes such as vectors, colors, and arrays. For example, if the attribute is a color, an ", {"text": ["index"], "type": "code"}, " value of ", {"text": ["0"], "type": "code"}, " returns the red component, ", {"text": ["1"], "type": "code"}, " returns the green component, and ", {"text": ["2"], "type": "code"}, " returns the blue component."]}], "indent": 0, "role": "item", "type": "usage", "text": [{"text": ["point(", {"text": ["surface_node"], "type": "var"}, ", ", {"text": ["point_number"], "type": "var"}, ", ", {"text": ["attribute"], "type": "var"}, ", ", {"text": ["index"], "type": "var"}, ")"], "type": "code"}]}], "container": true, "role": "item_group", "type": "usage_group"}, {"body": [{"body": [{"indent": 4, "type": "para", "text": ["This function will interpolate between point values if the point\n    number is fractional, such as 3.35"]}], "indent": 0, "role": "item", "type": "note"}], "container": true, "role": "item_group", "type": "note_group"}, {"body": [{"lang": "exp", "indent": 0, "type": "pre", "text": ["\npoint(\"/obj/geo1/facet1\", 3, \"P\", 0)\n"]}, {"indent": 0, "type": "para", "text": ["Returns the X component of point 3 of the facet1 surface node in geo1."]}, {"lang": "exp", "indent": 0, "type": "pre", "text": ["\npoint(\"/obj/geo1/facet1\", 3, \"N\", 2)\n"]}, {"body": [{"indent": 4, "type": "para", "text": ["facet1 surface node of object geo1."]}], "indent": 0, "type": "para", "text": ["Returns the Z component of the normal attribute of point 3 in the"]}], "indent": 0, "level": 1, "text": "Examples", "role": "section", "container": true, "type": "examples_section", "id": "examples"}, {"body": [{"body": [{"indent": 0, "blevel": 2, "type": "bullet", "text": [{"text": "", "value": "/expressions/pointavg", "fallback_text": "pointavg()", "fullpath": "/expressions/pointavg", "scheme": "Exp", "type": "link"}]}, {"indent": 0, "blevel": 2, "type": "bullet", "text": [{"text": "", "value": "/expressions/vertex", "fallback_text": "vertex()", "fullpath": "/expressions/vertex", "scheme": "Exp", "type": "link"}]}], "container": true, "type": "bullet_group"}], "indent": 0, "level": 1, "text": "Related", "role": "section", "container": true, "type": "related_section", "id": "related"}], "title": ["point"], "summary": ["Returns the value of a point attribute."], "attrs": {"category": "attributes", "type": "expression"}, "included": ["/expressions/_index_argument"], "type": "root"}